Zuma says Lipman was working alongside her late anti-apartheid activist husband Alan Lipman and will forever be remembered. JOHANNESBURG President Jacob Zuma has described Beata Lipman as a principled and esteemed freedom fighter and struggle veteran.Lipman, who died on Thursday at the age of 88, is known to be an architect of the Freedom Charter as she has organised information during the congress of the people in 1955 in Kliptown and drafted the original Freedom Charter in her own handwriting.Zuma says Lipman was working alongside her late anti-apartheid activist husband Alan Lipman and will forever be remembered.Presidency spokesperson Bongani Ngqulunga said, The president is saddened to have lost such a principled and esteemed fighter like Miss Lipman.&quot;